I wouldn't go back here or recommend the food or the service. Had 2 appetizers, the potstickers were very good, the cheese curds were good minus the over cooked ones that had exploded w no cheese inside, which was about half of them. Then ordered the salmon, tasted pretty good but it was overcooked, the rice was dry and the green beans w it were also overcooked almost mushy. Pretty sure the salmon was frozen and nit fresh. We had 2 orders of salmon at the table, both the same. Son had the cheeseburger w fries and a salad, that was good. Mom had the mac n cheese w lobster n shrimp. The lobster was like non existant and not enough cheese in it, so it wasn't creamy. More like eating semi-dry pasta. The waiter we had was very nice but very spacey and not very customer service oriented. His name was Zak. Told Zak the food was okay, he just said okay good back, and left.. lol. Had to ask him twice for lemons for my water. I ordered an amaretto sour. Probably the worst one I've had ever, hands down, and I'm 40. It tasted like they mixed water w it. I asked for a shot of amaretto to add to it bc it was so weak. Zak told me ya, we've heard that before, its because its only a 2 oz mix drink sorry...umm ok lol. Anyways the additional shot didn't make it taste any better, it tasted super flat like they hadn't changed the soda they added to it. So I told Zak that and he said he'd check w the bar tender. He came back and asked us like 10 mins later how everything was and if we needed anything, again, made no mention of my drink and brought us the check. So I asked, did the bartender say anything about this drink n why it tastes so bad? He said, ya, but that other lady left already that made your drink and the bartender now said she probably did her own thing instead of making it correctly. I said ok? And he just said sorry. Never offered to correct the drink and charged me 12 for it. Also had to ask this dude twice for cherries. Just a sad overall experience for a $150 meal and in my opinion not worth the price. If I wrote a short review it would say "overcooked food w poor customer service". Honestly, just go somewhere else.

My only experience with this restaurant. We stayed at Harrah’s hotel and casino last week. This restaurant was next door (separated by a walkway) We ordered from our room for pickup. We were told 15 minutes. I decided to get there early so that our food would not be waiting and getting cold, I arrived within 5 minutes (it was 2 minutes from our room. I paid and tipped the hostess. 10 minutes later she arrived from the kitchen with our carry out bag and a drink. I asked “what is this?” Referring to the drink. She replied “it’s a Sprite”. I said I didn’t order a drink. She replied “I know”. I asked because both hands were full are their utensils for 2 in the bag, she assured me there was. I returned to our room where we prepared to eat (we were starving after walking Nola). My wife asked about the drink and we had a chuckle about it. There was only one set of utensils. We had ordered an appetizer, steak, and wagyu beef burger. They forgot to put the appetizer in the bag, my steak that I had ordered medium rare was medium (I hate over cooked steak), my wife’s burger ordered medium was rare (she hates a rare burger). She took one bite and the blood ran into the bun, her appetite was ruined from that point on (she ate nothing else). My steak was served as a single over cooked piece of meat in a plastic dish about 4 times the size of the steak. The steak was cold. I was hungry and so ate the steak by picking it up (it was too tough to cut), I ate it by dipping it into catchup (the only way I can eat an over cooked steak). I then called the restaurant to complain about the entire disappointment. The manager said our appetizer was there waiting for us. I refused to accept an appetizer that had been setting and outlined with him as I’ve done here the list of grievances with the entire experience. His only offer was to remake the entire meal for us and then to say that he was sure we would not be interested in that, at which point I agreed. The place looked very inviting, I was very excited to try it as I love craft beer. What a complete and total disappointment. It should have been a complete refund and a “let us make it up to you”. As it is I will never return and will tell others of our experience.

We stopped in for a beer on the way home and ended up spending the evening watching the Sugar Bowl, sipping on their delicious Märzen and eventually adding some potstickers and garlic fries. The potstickers were good, but the sweet chili sauce was so tasty we dipped our fries in it too!! The fries were kinda oily, but good flavor. Service was awesome and all in all I would recommend and totally come back here!

This is what I emailed GB corporate.  I will not be going back to GB.  To whom this may concern, I have been an avid proponent of Gordon Biersch.  I have ordered take out from your restaurant at least three times a month.  So, to say my recent experience with your company was disappointing, is an understatement.  On November 21, 2020 I placed an order from Gordon Biersch through the Postmates App for my husband’s birthday.  I proceeded to wait about 1.5 hours when I received a phone call from my Postmates Driver.  She was currently still waiting at Gordon Biersch for my food, and she asked me if I had received my food already. I responded, confused, with a no, and that I was about to reach out to them on why my order was taking so long.  I could hear her tell the people at GB what I said and she tells me well they gave your food to someone else, so they are going to put a rush order in to remake my food and get it out to me.  At this time I understood that mistakes happened, I thanked them and we hung up.  About five minutes later my driver calls me back and informs me that GB changed their mind and they weren’t going to remake anything because they would lose out on the sale. They said if I wanted my money I could follow up with Postmates.  Now, this is the frustrating and disappointing part of this experience.  GB gave my food to the wrong person. That wasn’t the fault of Postmates, my driver, or me. However, instead of fixing their mistake and incompetence to ensure the food went to the right people, I was nonchalantly informed that they would not be fixing this issue. So, here I am at 9 pm, no food, a hungry husband and seven year old, because of a mistake GB made, no one else.  I have loved this company for my entire adult life. However, after this experience, I am reluctant, if not entirely turned off to ever ordering or dining at GB again.  Any decent manager would have seen to having this issue fixed, especially since it was their mistake, no one else’s.  I do not normally reach out to corporations like this, but this was especially angering when I was told they were going to fix the issue, but then countered their previous statement, because they were going to be out the $50 I spent.  It’s not about the money, it’s about the principle, and if these are the values and responses of GB, well then my business with GB is over.  I’m disappointed that any business would handle an issue, such as this, with zero professionalism and commitment to their patrons. Without patrons your business would not exist.  Very Respectfully, Samantha Abbruzzi

This is my favorite brewery in the area. The food is amazing and the beer is to die for. The servers are also top notch. I’ve been here so often I have a rewards card now.
Great food, great beer, great service, and all around great environment! You should try the cheese curds and the Winter Boch is out of this world.
Great place to eat.  They make their own beer on site.  Park at Harrah's garage and they will validate it.
Perfection on my grilled tuna and my wife's chicken schnitzel were great!! Garlic fries was the perfect side. Totally recommended.

Chargrilled Oysters were amazing but they ran out of Raw Oysters very early in the night. Service was very slow, we were told to expected an hour wait time, it was to just shy of two hours because the text system was not working correctly.

Service was great. Food was good too except the first pretzel which came out ice cold but they brought another one and it was great, too. Enjoyed the cocktails and the game. Go cowboys. When we come back to New Orleans again, we will likely come back again.

We've been to many different GB in different states, this one is ok in comparison. Host mismanages tables. Telling people there is an hour and a half wait chases customers away. Within 45 minutes there were NUMEROUS empty tables. Turnover isn't 90 minutes. We sat in the bar area with community type tables within minutes. Service was ok, food and beer was good as usual.
The worst services I have ever gotten from them
Service is great food is delicious
Great fresh beer! Pretty good food!! Second time there weeks apart, and still nice and fast service. Keep it up!!
The food, the service and the atmosphere were great. We definitely walked out of there very satisfied
Definitely would recommend the garlic fries to share. The beers that they have on tap are excellent and come in a variety of sizes. Would highly recommend.
A good place to grab a drink & watch a sporting event. The bar area has tons of TVs and the food and service are good.
Good food, service could be better

I had the BEST steak tonight, the service was amazing.  All of the food that we had was delicious, we even asked if we could speak to the head chef, this handsome young man came to our table Chef Andrew Myers we thanked him and told him how delicious all of the food was.  He was the nicest young man (totally a southern gentleman)!!! So again, thank you Chef, it was definitely one of our highlights in New Orleans, and we will be back!!!!

Hands down the best place for a large group.  We had our annual Christmas party there last night, our 2nd at Gordon Biersch. Everyone raved over their food choice and the atmosphere. Love the large private rooms.  Chief Andrew even came out and wished all a Merry Christmas/Happy Holidays 😃

We had the private dinning area for our SSS Christmas party Saturday night and had the best time. The waitress and waiters were fabulous! The food was spectacular Chief Drew knocked it out of the park! Really really enjoyed it!
The food was absolutely amazing! Our group had an awesome time last night and had the 2 best waitresses ever!!
I've been here many times and the food is always very good. I've had 2 club Christmas dinners here and we have NO complaints whatsoever.  Very organized and professional staff.
One bad server

I've always like this restaurant and have been coming for over twelve years now. The Heffeweisen and Marzen beers are some of the best I've ever tried. The menu is massive and there is something for everyone.
Service was great and food was awesome

Good beer selection, knowledgeable bartenders. I was in the mood for a burger and the gastro pub burger that was recommended did not disappoint. I sat at the bar with other solo diners and felt comfortable. I fell into easy conversations with complete strangers. Overall great experience.
Great food, great service ......nacho appetizer was incredible and double bacon burger with fries was great.  Highly recommend
Pretty busy when we were there, but still got our food fast. Full menu, you'll find something you like. Really impressed with the beers, all that I tried were excellent
Good food excellent service.
Great place!
THE FRIES!!!!!
The food is very good
We got there right as they opened.  Our waitress was awesome and helped us decide how to spend the rest of our day.  Burger and boneless wings were good.
Went here for some drinks. The drinks were good, service was mediocre.

Tooo toooo salty.  Tuna almost unbearable. Very kind server.  Had a great mule.  Next time, I will order no salt on food.  Presented beautifully.  The server thinks it was salted butter blend used in prep.  Nice place.  Gave us bread pudding as appology.
Great sports bar.  Highly competent and very friendly bartenders.
Awesome food. Very good prices!
Super great service, nice atmosphere excellent food.
Food and drinks were awesome. Our server, Kym, kept his cool during a busy rush, and kept us informed on the specials going on so we could get the best they had to offer. Loved our visit!
not gluten free friendly at all. separate menu basically says skip the bun, omit the fries and doesn’t describe the food so you have to cross reference with the regular menu.
Only had a martini but it was very tasty.
Quite enjoy my burger and beer.
Delicious variety of foods.  Something for everyone.  One suggestion... Turn down the music.
Good beers, good apps
Good beer, good food and good service
Ate there twice while we were in New Orleans. First class food. Great beer. Great service. One place I'll definitely be back to. 👍😁🍺
Good food good drink only around at 11pm to get a good burger after drinking friendly waitresses also.
Excellent service and burgers, the french fries are delicious.
This place is a must. The food and beer is outstanding. The service is friendly with a great atmosphere. Nicely priced food and beer best in area. $$
Good wings
Awesome, as always

First and last time at Gordan Biersch. It was very disappointing  I will never go there again. Food and service was terrible. Everything that we ordered was salty. We had to sent back one of our meals because it was not edible. The waitress messed up our order and check. We were charged twice for the soups and food. Please double check your bill. I would NOT recommend this place to anyone!
Best nachos I have ever tasted but it was way too noisy
Try the southwest eggrolls, went back the next day for more. Great service.

Good: Excellent variety of food and drinks in the menu. The food looks, smells, and is delicious. Courteous staff. The place looks great, is clean, and there's plenty of room from one table to the other(s). So, you eat comfortable. Bad: I found nothing wrong or bad during my visit. I highly recommend it.
Great bar food and terrific martinis
Fun Mustard topping and beer collection
Was good but not as good as other gordon biersch's we been to.   Still loved the eggroll appetizer and their burgers.   Staff was extremely pleasant.

The food is amazing and cooked to perfection. Even a late night menu brought out one of the most excellent meals I've had. To match the beer is craft and authentic. The bratwurst is comparable to what we have had in Germany.
Great service!!  Do yourself a favor and get the nachos.
Real good food and beer.  Tuesdays are all day happy hour. Sarah was our server and she was awesome

Was expecting a fantastic Bloody Mary, but the amazing beer greatly made up for it. Our pretzel was burnt when it came out, but they quickly brought us a perfect fresh one. Red beans and rice were completely to my liking. Service was wonderful. Price was better than expected for lunch time. We will be back.
Nice brews
The steak was pretty good. Probably as good as the one that costs 3 times as much at the place next door.
Love GB burgers, garlic fries, crab dip and service. Taylor was awesome!!

Gordon plays the spoons everything 3rd Tuesday here. His brother Cameron plays the French harp, his sister plays the ringing tambourine, he's momma can't hear the music but she reads his lips and help the family sing. That little band is all a part of living and their only means of living at the time but it isn't like any family combo because daddy Frank the guitar man is blind.
Nice food and ambience
Food was amazing, but beer selection is lacking.
Look, it's overpriced, but it's good. The food is prepared well and is tasty but the price is inflated due to location.
Great beer, free parking, and the cheese curds are killer.
The food and service was great!
Great management and bartenders
Very good steak
Very nice clean restaurant. The people working were very friendly. The service was great. The food was great. There was 6 of us with 6 different dishes. All smiles!

Excellent chicken wings and slider burgers, Gordon biersch is always a fun environment with great food and drinks our waiter was super courteous and awesome server, Thanks Gordon Biersch for a great evening
They have changed policy for paid parking. Spend $20. Maxium time 4 hours.

Nice selection of beer, but pretty overpriced food selection. For our beer flight, it wasn't even given on a paddle -- meaning we just carried the glasses to our table not knowing which was which. We received a freebie flight beer, which was nice of the bartender. This alone would've earned the establishment 3 stars.  HOWEVER, at the bottom of a flight glass was something quite disgusting. Imagine mucus gone old and grey -- and on your lip after you finished the glass. So yeah, slightly traumatized now.

I needed a quick bite for lunch and I'm glad I stopped in. Ordered the veggie burgers with a side of mashed potatoes. It was great, especially the mashed potatoes (not from the box). I will be back. Also the hostesses were beautiful inside and out.
Good beer, great service, and the food is top notched

Such an awesome bar set up with the garage doors. Not too pricey and all of the beers are made by them. I love being able to see into the brewing room from my spot on the bar. The food was a little pricey for the portions that they gave but the beer was great. The staff was amazing too. The location of this spot is top notch.

Earl was such a great help when selecting our drinks. We arrived shortly after opening, yet he was quick to serve us. Deducted one star because the California Beach Taco had barely any fish on it, the flavor of the cod I did get was was great but the taco mostly consisted of cabbage and tortilla.
Unforgettable french fries!
Excellent beers, my Burger was Amazing.
The food was absolutely delicious. I can't wait to come back to try more. The beers were top notch. Up to 5 free samples per person, and the Hefeweizen is my favorite.
Great food and beer. Our waiter was the best would recommend it and go back

Ordered via Grubhub....don't expect perfection with delivery but, seriously?! Soooo much salt on the pretzel it was inedible, chicken schnitzel had absolutely no flavor whatsoever (but the sauce was good), and cheese curds were a mass of over fried batter with all the cheese fried out....basically a couple large mashed of fried breading! Very dissapointed!

My mom and I had two different starters. Blue crab and artichoke dip and calamari, they were very delicious food. Then my mom and I came back for lunch on Saturday. The fish and chips were delicious. My mom had sausage platter that was good also.

Ordered: One Brewer's steak, Cooked Medium-Well - that's all I wanted for protein.  Received: Major undercook. One Brewer's steak, cooked Medium-Rare (Borderline Rare).  I've attached the steak cooking chart, and a picture of my steak. The order was through grub-hub and delivered to hotel.  I did not receive the side order requested, Garlic Fries. No leaning-forward attitude, disappointed customer = poor review. I'm sorry I had to write this as I would have preferred to give you a great review after receiving great food and service.
Ok
The beer I had was good. Oktoberfest
Excellent service and food, the beer wasn't bad either
Nice bar area... great Hefeweizen!
Everything was amazing! Service was excellent! We had a wide variety of food and beers, but would have been happy with just a beer and the garlic fries; the scent alone is glorious!

2nd time here. Nice environment, ordered from the late night menu. I chose poorly as the Blue Oyster dip dish thingee I had was a terrible mush of I don't know what. I'd expect better from a restaurant if this type.

Was told there was an hour wait so we sat at the bar and were immediately served. Chose the Kobe burger with garlic fried and some wings. Enjoyed it all.  Was attended to by 2 different bartenders and while I didn't get either of their names, both were friendly and attentive.
Really grate, although a very busy place, service was good...and food too...
Food was great!
Brianna was our server and was fantastic. Excellent service.
Good burger and fair beers.

My family and I love visiting GB. The food is absolutely delicious: I prefer the Brewer's Steak but the schnitzels are popular as well. Great beers. And, most importantly, reasonable prices. If your visiting NOLA and want a $20 meal as good as the local $50 meals,  GB is the right place.
Burger was great and beer prices are decent.
Very slow service when its crowded
We sat in the bar area and had great service and wonderful appetizers.  Asian chicken bite and Asiago fries were a huge hit. We devoured them!
Great late night bartender fantastic service. Great spot for a last minute nightcap or a quick nosh for those staying in nearby hotels.
In-house brewed craft beer Great happy hour food and drink.

Well first we waited forever to get service. Then the food was subpar at best. Chicken wings were greasy and no flavor. California Flatbread pizza was ok but I have had better. Beer was ok but had a bad after taste, had the blonde. Would not come back.

I frequent GB pretty often for a meal for lunch to go. I went away from my normal burger or wings and ordered the Lobster Pasta. It was so full of grease we could not even eat it. Draining it did not even help. Im not sure if it was too much olive oil or butter but it was a horrible experience. The bar food and the grilled foods are great but the $25 spent on the lobster pasta was a waste of my money.
Have had two really good meals here. Get the 5 flight of beers to try the different types.

I want to start off and say that the rating is not a result of the server Jody she was fantastic!!!  We ordered beer and it was good but they did not offer the stout in a sampler because it’s too “expensive” to put in a sampler cup. If a resturant doesn’t want to offer a sampler cup of a beer they’ve brew because of “cost” then something is wrong.  My friend ordered the Cajun pasta for $20+ and the portion was not up to “Louisiana” standards. It was small and pricy and not worth the cost.  I ordered bruschetta chicken. My food came out wrong the first time and needed to Be remade. The remake was speedy but the pasta with the basalmic vingarette was too much. I do not recommend as a dish.
Nice atmosphere and attentive staff. Great selection of authentic german beers.
Good service..& food..

Conveniently located right across the street from the convention center, this location has ample space to host large groups. As you would expect there is a tremendous beer selection and variety of menu items that should satisfy most guests.
It has nice and fast service but the food is average and could be better
Beer was good.  The pretzel and sausage appetizer was decent, but the burger was mediocre at best.  I don't have a desire to return.
By N Orleans standards not great. Fish was dry and tough. Noisy
Here for a function, very good food, drinks and service.

I just wasn't that impressed with the food I had here for lunch. There is just better food elsewhere in New Orleans. I don't know if dinner is any better but I would pass on this place for lunch.  The beer they had was the only redeeming part of the establishment.
The staff was really nice. Brussel sprouts were great, as was pizza. Crusty wine glass... not so great.
Great place and food
Great food and great service! We will definitely be back!
They somehow lost our credit card when paying the bill.  They called later saying they found it but overall handled the situation poorly.

My wife and I shared a steak which had great flavor and melted in our mouths. The potato options had too much garlic for my tastes. Our server was on the ball. Oh, and they even split our sides and steak before they brought them to the table.
Best burgers I ever had. 🍺 isn't bad either.
A good place to hang out, have some nice food and friendly service.
Good food, friendly staff
Watch 2015 college football semi final here. Fantastic atmosphere. Service was OK, food kind of average but perhaps OK for a sports match - NOT for dining an sich.
A beer drinkers paradise with nice people and good happy hour nibbles.

Best beer and best food I have had in New Orleans! What a great brewery. The Citra IPA was amazing...so good, had to take a growler back to the hotel. Andrew was the best bartender ever. He provided excellent service and made for a great outing experience. Can't wait to go back!
Food was great- really nice variety with a great beer- wine & great menu!! Our server was amazing super knowledgeable about not only the food/beverage but also the local area-

Good food. I had grilled redfin which was delicious and flavorful. My husband had a Kobe burger and two servings of the garlic fries. Waitress was friendly and always ready to help. But we were seated in a direct line from the entrance which left me freezing cold the entire meal. Restroom was in need of attention.
mediocre burger,  pizza not bad.
Delicious food, awesome service

Great place to watch the game, it was packed. We had tacos and the crab artichoke dip, they were both delicious. The flight of beer was great, lots of variety. Our waiter was super nice and gave us some great stops to check out in our travels around the city.
Food and drinks were good.  The choices on the happy hour menu weren't extensive so we ordered off the regular menu. Fun place to watch football.

Walked In and got a table for lunch quickly. Good selection of beers and fun cocktails. We ordered three appetizers and split them between two people which was still way too much food. The pretzel and nachos are great. The major improvement could be in service- we waited more than ten minutes for the check and another ten to get it returned. Also the tables are pretty wobbly which adds an annoying touch.

Been there several times. They do have some really good beer and the staff is very friendly and well educated on what they serve. A wide range of food choices all of which are tasty. Oh and least I forget a great place to watch football.
Waiter was great, food mot so much. Sent back my calamari and drinks took forever to get.
The Lobster Mac n cheese tho!!! 👍👍
Garlic fries to die for!
The calamari is horrible! So over cooked it was like eating a rock

I rated this restaurant 1 star because I could not rate it any lower.  Our waiter Michael was great.  The food however,  was not. I ordered the chicken, bacon, avocado on flat bread. It was lacking of chicken,  bacon and avocado.  It was about 12 inches long,  quartered, with about a teaspoon of each ingredient on the whole flatbread. I talked to the manager, Heather, whom didn't think it was a problem.  She stated that it was proportioned to the companies guidelines. $12. Wasn't worth  $2. Also the Crab and artichoke dip was lacking in flavor.  Would not recommend at all.

We stood in line 20 minutes to wait for a table, right as they were seating us a large group of guys grabbed our table and waiter said they cannot ask people to get up, I said that is ridiculous, you have a line of people waiting to be seated.  Took 30 min to take our order, no salt and pepper on table, sweetner for tea, finally got drinks, they never brought our beers out, we never got refills, I ordered the grilled chicken kabobs, they were awful, not grilled at all, vegtables were raw, no pineapple on them as advertised, vegtables were raw. Rice hard and undercooked.  Waiter had an attitude!  my food arrived cold, we had a show to catch so as slow as the service was... just a tough break and bad experience, would not reccomend ..From the looks of a ton of really bad reviews, management might consider an overhaul!! This place is terrible!

Fun place that I have been to over the years! Great location and they will even validate your parking garage tickets! The past two times I have been, the service has be great, the food sub par. For the price, I expected more. I ordered the chicken with beer sauce which came with green beans which were practically raw. The chicken was good, but a smaller portion as compared to the sides it was served with. After talking with the others I ate with, we all remarked that the portions were small and the food was bland.

Staff is is nice that is why I give the one star.  The wife order a bloody Mary, and was told that it was a Cajun bloody Mary..far from it. She also ordered the Cajun pasta, tomato sauce with no flavor. I ordered a burger medium/well, it was like I said extra well done. Severe let down from the quality I expect from this restaurant
Taco Thursday is great, the shrimp and lobster tacos there are amazing.

2 stars for good bar service, value of food and happy hour beer. Great beer taste. -3 stars for failure of management to properly honor a survey coupon code and address my concerns and speak to me to resolve issues. I left unsatisfied, feeling taken advantage of for a few cents store profit, and not valued as a regular customer. I will return but will be visiting another restaurant for Monday dinner.
Place was pretty crowded with only one seat at the bar. Didn't try any of the food so I can't comment on that but the citra IPA I had was amazing.

We were completely shocked by the level of service from a chain restaurant!  (I'm normally anti-chain, but we were hungry and the restaurant was there). Our server, Josh, was AWESOME! Since we had never been there before, he offered to get us small samples of the beers that he thought we would like (based on a few questions on what kind of beer we normally drank). Food was also really good .   i would definitely go back
Gitthe yellowfin tuna, it was amazing. Buddy got the pizza, it was OK, crust needs improvement. Still 5 stars!!
Wings didn't have much flavor even with the sauce.  The crabmeat dip was ok,  crabmeat kinda hidden.

My food, beer, and service was great. The only thing about this place is that it isn't an authentic New Orleans experience. If you don't mind that, this is a good place for a diverse menu and a variety of beers. If you are here for tourism, go spend your limited time here at one of the local legends. If you're here for work or etc. and just want good beer and food, look no further.
Good food, wings are excellent
Amazing food and great prices. Cocktails are made well and delicious. Been here 2 in two days!
All the sliders were awesome and the bartender Scott was great, with awesome advice about the area
Great burger, garlic fries and Buffalo wings

After almost 30 minutes wait to receive our food it was all lukewarm.  I had the cblt, which had to dlbe deconstructed because the onion straws were so cd the left a oily film on the roof of my mouth.  We had to chase down the "server" to get our bill.
It was ok. Only tasty thing here were the adult beverages. Outdoor sitting was very nice though.

What a disappointment. The mussels (large size) are NOT large enough as a meal, despite what the wait staff says. They were lukewarm and VERY salty. I would not recommend them. Service was mediocre at best, we were seated in the bar area, and it seemed we were more of an inconvenience than a customer. The only reason it gets a single star is the beer.  We were also here for a group function the other night and the wings weren't great, the pizza was "meh," and the fries were bland.

Food was good; however servers were disinterested and ready to close, despite closing time being over an hour away on a Monday night.  Disappointing given the cost spent on dinner for family of 4.  If trying to close early we would have rather just been told as much when we walked in vs. feeling like an inconvenience.

The worst. Maybe because we went at at 9 P.M. Ordered the steak, well done. When the steak came out it was still "moo-ing". Ordered the beef taco, which is not shredded. It was 3 taco's with 1 peice of steak. Ordered the pepperoni pizza which was good.  Ordered a garden salad, it was warm and the dressing was watery.
Good burgers, fries a bit on the salty side.
Garlic fries are amazing. Wait staff was wonderful. Enjoyed or dinner!
Great Service even better food

Gordon Biersch brews decent beer and has a nice selection of food. It is a run of the mill brewpub chain; but when nothing else is open and you're hungry at night this is a great place to go. Servers were not necessarily friendly, but they were attentive. Overall I had a pleasant dinner.
Had the Southwest Nachos.......one of the best things ever!!!!! Also had shrimp and lobster tacos, excellent as well!
Enjoyed the good beer and great food. We brought our little maltipoo to the patio. Friendly service. Very good atmosphere.
Great Experience!!! Best egg rolls in the world!

(Translated by Google) It is a restaurant and brewery with the distillery in sight, so you have a variety of beer to choose from. The attention was correct and the food very good. We sat outside in the renovated Fulton Passage and had a great time. All the passage is recovered and in that block it is pedestrian with a bar next to each other. It is a great place to go to dinner or have a few drinks.  (Original) Es un restaurant y  cervecería con la destilería a la vista, por lo que tenes mucha variedad de cerveza para elegir. La atención fue correcta y la comida muy buena. Nos sentamos afuera, en el renovado pasaje Fulton y lo pasamos muy bien. Todo el pasaje esta recuperado y en esa cuadra es peatonal con un bar al lado del otro. Es un gran lugar para ir a cenar o tomar unos tragos.
Excellent beer great beer good prices.
Good food love it every time never had any problems. I've been going for years.
Service was bad, sat by the hostess she didn't say a word. Ordered chicken wings asked for extra crispy they came soggy. Did not get the burger I ordered burger....Thx but no thx.

I was in town back in 2014 for Wrestlemania 30 I stopped in here for a bite to eat it's a nice place to eat if like me you are not a fan of seafood.  I really liked the garlic fries and the ultimate double chocolate cake.  I'll be back in NOLA next year for Wrestlemania 34 may have to stop in again.
Great food and great location.
